Line 142: CpsGroovyShell trusted = new CpsGroovyShellFactory(null).forTrusted().build();
Line 143: new CpsGroovyShellFactory(null).withParent(trusted).withSandbox(true).build().getClassLoader().parseClass(value);

The getClassLoader() returns CleanGroovyClassLoader which extends GroovyClassLoader.
The CpsGroovyShell.parse() method (which calls doParse()) wraps compilation in GroovySandbox.Scope:
  private Script doParse(GroovyCodeSource codeSource) throws CompilationFailedException {
      GroovySandbox sandbox = new GroovySandbox();
      ...
      try (GroovySandbox.Scope scope = sandbox.enter()) {
          return super.parse(codeSource);
      }
  }

But parseClass() is called on the raw GroovyClassLoader, bypassing doParse() entirely. The GroovySandbox.Scope is never entered, so compile-time code execution (AST transforms, @Grab) is not restricted.

